monsties.descrip: placid, crested herbivorous monsters. They form herds and raise their young as a community.
alpha monsters that lead the smaller Velociprey. Note their larger size, impressive frill, and sharper claws.
bear-like monsters found in warm, damp environments. Can often be found catching fish from rivers.
Monsters boasting ample beaks and fan-like ears that splay open when angered. Konchu are a staple food.
A Yian Kut-Ku subspecies. Their blue coloration and physical prowess set them apart from their pink kin.
herd-forming Herbivores covered in long, thick fur. Popo meat is nutritious and prized by gourmands.
white Fanged Beasts with acute hearing. They slide on the ice at high speeds to chase down their prey.
powerful alpha monsters that lead Bullfango herds. They mow down their prey with their sturdy tusks.
amphibian monsters known for the astonishing changes that occur when they coat their bodies in icy armor.
loathsome flying wyverns dwelling mainly in caves. They generate and release electricity to deadly effect.
khezu subspecies with red bodies. Its electrical power is far more advanced than that of its white cousin.
herbivores clad in sturdy, armor-like plates. Approach with caution to avoid a fierce and persistent chase.
alpha monsters that lead Genprey. Paralyzing venom tips their highly-developed fangs and claws.
royal ludroth use their sponge-like neck scales to absorb water and prevent dehydration.
crested Bird Wyverns. They strike their crests to generate blinding flashes and dazzle their enemies.
temnocerans that build nests of sticky webbing to ensnare prey, which they rend with their mandibles.
temnocerans that inhabit desert areas. They lurk beneath the sands in order ambush unwary prey.
Bird Wyverns with colourful plumage. Using thoracic vocal organs they imitate the calls of other monsters.
female flying wyverns dubbed Queens of the Land. Possess powerful legs, and deadly, poisonous tails.
a vivid, pink-scaled Rathian subspecies. Its tail attacks are far more powerful than those of a regular Rathian.
barroth bury themselves in mud, but will not hesitate to attack those who disturb them in their bogs.
alpha monster that lead Cephalos. Hardened black scales set them apart from the smaller Cephalos.
feared as tyrants of the deserts, these Flying Wyverns attack any who stray into their territory.
a formidable subspecies of Diablos. Females darken in the mating season so as to warn off other creatures.
primeval in appearance, these Flying Wyverns are possessed of fearsome limbs, jaws and claws.
alpha monsters that lead Ioprey. Their poison sacs allow them to attack by spitting an acrid venom.
juvenile form of a Gravios. Its most distinctive feature is the rock-hard carapace on its back.
flying wyverns that inhabit volcanic regions. Capable of attacking with fiery breath and sleeping gas.
brute Wyverns with mighty jaws. They spray the stones and ore which stick to them in deadly, explosive attacks.
a black Tigrex subspecies. The force and range of its howl is even more fearsome than that of its cousins.
alpha monsters that lead Jaggi. They issue complex commands to the pack via their howls.
fanged beasts with limbs well adapted to swinging through the forest tree areas they inhabit.
a subspecies of Royal Ludroth. Poison is stored in their spongy purple manes.
bird wyvern known for their hard shells and long manes. Aggressive, prone to attack unprovoked.
pink-furred fanged beasts. They let rip with almighty farts, the stench of which overwhelms opponents.
a green-furred Congalala. Able to store even more prodigious quantities of gas than its pink brethren.
subspecies with vibrant red plumage. Flints in its wings allow it to release fearsome electrical attacks.
this subspecies has a tough, black carapace. It is capable of discharging powerful blasts of heat.
fanged wyverns that store the electrical energy of the countless Thunderbugs that they gather.
basarios subspecies that coats its carapace with rare ore. It scatters this with great force during battle.
flying wyverns residing in wooded areas. Fearfully fast, persistent, and sly, they excel at hunting prey.
dappled green fur serves as camouflage in the deep forests that this Nargacuga calls home.
Dubbed the King of the Skies, it dominates battle with its powerful wings and poison-tipped claws.
a rathalos subspecies. More mobile than its cousin, it attacks with a matchless speed and ferocity.
a subspecies of Gypceros with a uniquely colored hide. It attacks by spitting highly venomous waste.
this subspecies has pale, multicolored fur. They make sport of their prey with the cunning of their attacks.
leviathans atop the aquatic food chain, due in no small part to their ability to deliver electrical shocks.
leviathans atop the aquatic food chain, due in no small part to their ability to deliver electrical shocks.
brute wyverns that roam in search of food. Ferocious in the extreme, and relentless in pursuit of prey.
bluish-white, crested Bird Wyverns. Their ruthless cunning makes them natural leaders of Baggi packs.
a subspecies of Barroth. Often seen in polar regions, bashing their crowns against the ice.
flying wyverns that rule the frozen wastes. Spikily scaled wings and tail allow them to run effortlessly across ice.
a subspecies of Barioth. Its breath is strong enough to generate tornados among the desert sands.
feeding on Dracophage Bugs has given this subspecies access to unheard of brute strength.
brute wyvern coated in a volatile substance. Its saliva can be used to ignite this coat, with explosive results.
ultra-aggressive Fanged Beasts. Widely regarded as the pinnacle in unparalleled physical prowess.
lightning-wielding mystical creature. Classified as an Elder Dragon, but its true nature remains a mystery.
endowed with an impressive cranial horn. It uses its horn in brutal attacks, screeching ear-splitting war cries.
flying wyvern known for its lustrous golden scales. Its scales can be launched at prey in high-speed attacks.
a rare Rathian subspecies. Its majestic golden sheen resembles the glow of the full moon.
a rare Rathalos subspecies. Its piercing silver shimmer resembles the blazing sun.

a rare Tigrex subspecies. Its existence is unconfirmed due to lack of reliable, and living, eye-witness accounts.
mythical beasts that few have encountered. It is said that temperatures around them plummet below zero.
